\chapter{Token Definitions of KAPAOOW}\label{app:tokens}

The table below shows the the token definitions. The first column is the token type which is simply a name for reference, the second column is a regular expression for how the token is recognized by the scanner, and the third column shows which of the tokens are non-significant.

The order of the tokens is the order which the scanner will try to match the regular expression to a token. Taking one of the top tokens and moving it $n$ rows down would mean iterating $n$ more times to find a match.

All token definitions are case insensitive.

